<item>
            <title>[OAK-983] Non full-text indices should ignore queries that have full-text constraints</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-983</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The PropertyIndex and the NodeTypeIndex don&apos;t take into account existing full-text constraints on a query and can return a smaller cost, making the query engine incorrectly choose the wrong index for a full-text query.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12666335">OAK-983</key>
            <summary>Non full-text indices should ignore queries that have full-text constraints</summary>
